Content:
it depends:
- in France PhD students are paid 1400‚Ç¨-2000‚Ç¨/month, tuition is about 400‚Ç¨/year, so financial value is not a problem here.
- on whether the PhD is fundamental research vs applied research, sometimes the final results of applied researches PhD / postdoc are working products that have medium to high Technology readiness level.

Author: Cryptoon#3362
Content: @PHBA2061 not really sure how you think even 2k/month is worth putting a carreer on hold for 5 years without any other benefits to that later career though :p

Author: Cryptoon#3362
Content: As I said, the times a phd actually offers a benefit for later job opportunities are far smaller than when it does

Author: PHBA2061#2530
Content: in France and EU in general  it's quite different though, compared to PhD programs in the USA, PhD programs in France only take 3 years to complete (because the requirement here is PhD students must acquired an master diploma or a engineering diploma before applying for PhD program), the PhD thesis topic must be chosen/identified during the application process, it's like a job interview, only 1 student get selected, most of the time their thesis topics are already chosen beforehand by the research director, and their researches are funded by organisations or/and companies. So I would say PhD students in France & in EU in general have better preparations & have a clear vision of what they're going to do for their PhD program.
